// 1. The provider receives an ISO string (e.g., "2025-05-21T00:05:19.462Z")
// 2. It strips the 'Z' -> "2025-05-21T00:05:19.462"
// 3. It parses this Z-stripped string with `new Date()`, which interprets it as local time.
